Risk Management Program
Executive Summary
ConAgra Foods - Food Service Company
4530 Mobile Highway
Montgomery, Alabama 36108

I.    Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at ConAgra Foods ? Food Service Company (ConAgra) for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This Program summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The Risk Management Plan (RMP) is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including:
?    Introduction;
?    ConAgra policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
?    Hazard Assessment;
?    Prevention Program;
?    Five-Year Accident History;
?    Emergency Response Plan; 
?    Emergency Communications;
?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
?    Planned changes to improve safety; and
?    Management Program

II.    ConAgra?s Policies To Protect Health, Environment and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at ConAgra; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. ConAgra is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is ConAgra?s policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.

